# 🗄️ Data Structures: Hash Tables & Hashing

Notes on the computer science primitives powering modern high-speed databases, caches, and key-value stores.

## Core Mechanics
* **Time Complexity:** Average-case lookup, insertion, and deletion run in $O(1)$ constant time. Worst-case runs in $O(n)$ if the hash function is poor and causes massive collisions.
* **Hash Function:** A deterministic algorithm that maps input data of any size to a fixed-size integer value.

## Handling Hash Collisions
When two distinct keys compute to the exact same array index, the system must resolve the conflict:
1. **Separate Chaining:** Buckets contain pointers to linked lists. Colliding items are simply appended to the list at that index.
2. **Linear Probing:** The system sequentially scans the array forward from the collision point until it encounters an open memory slot.

